
You are given an integer `n` denoting the number of cities in a country. The cities are numbered from `0` to `n - 1`. You are also given a 2D integer array `roads` where <code>roads[i] = [a<sub>i</sub>, b<sub>i</sub>]</code> denotes that there exists a **bidirectional** road connecting cities <code>a<sub>i</sub></code> and <code>b<sub>i</sub></code>.
